<h1 id="what-about-other-tracking-technologies">What about other tracking technologies?</h1>

<p>Cookies are not the only way to recognize or track users of our Website. We may use similar technologies like web beacons (sometimes called ‚Äútracking pixels‚Äù or ‚Äúclear gifs‚Äù). These are tiny graphics files that contain a unique identifier that enable us to recognize when you‚Äôve visited our Website or opened an email that we sent you.</p>

<h1 id="opting-out-of-cookies">Opting out of cookies</h1>

<p>We provide you with choice over the use of cookies as described in this policy, however our Website may not work correctly if you change certain preferences, such as disabling all cookies.</p>

<p>To see what cookies have been set on your device and how to manage and delete them, visit <a href="https://www.allaboutcookies.org/">AllAboutCookies.org</a>.</p>

<h2 id="browser-level-cookie-controls">Browser-level cookie controls</h2>

<p>Most browsers allow you to manage cookie settings. These settings can usually be found in the ‚ÄòSettings‚Äô, ‚ÄòOptions‚Äô or ‚ÄòPreferences‚Äô menu of your browser.</p>

